## ðŸ—ï¸ **Constructor in Java**

### ðŸ“˜ Definition:
> Constructor ek special method hota hai jo **object create hote hi call** hota hai â€” aur uska kaam hota hai **object ko initialize karna**.

---

## ðŸ”‘ Features of Constructor:
| Point | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| ðŸ”¹ Name same as class name hota hai
| ðŸ”¹ **Return type nahi hota** (na `void`, na koi aur)
| ðŸ”¹ **Automatically call** hota hai object banate waqt
| ðŸ”¹ Object ko **initial values dene** ke liye use hota hai

---

## ðŸ§ª Example: Constructor Use

```java
public class Student {
    String name;
    int age;

    // Constructor
    public Student(String n, int a) {
        name = n;
        age = a;
    }

    public void show() {
        System.out.println("Name: " + name + ", Age: " + age);
    }
}
```

```java
// Usage
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s1 = new Student("Aman", 21);
        s1.show();  // Output: Name: Aman, Age: 21
    }
}
```

---

## ðŸ‘‡ Types of Constructors:

### 1. ðŸ†“ **Default Constructor** (No-arg constructor)
Java khud banata hai agar tu koi constructor nahi likhta.

```java
public Student() {
    System.out.println("Default constructor called");
}
```

### 2. ðŸ“¦ **Parameterized Constructor**
Jisme arguments pass karte ho:

```java
public Student(String name, int age) {
    this.name = name;
    this.age = age;
}
```

---

## ðŸ’¡ Why use Constructor?
- Object banate waqt hi values deni ho to
- Repeated code avoid karne ke liye
- Specific state mein object chahiye ho

---

## ðŸ”„ Difference: Constructor vs Method

| Constructor                  | Method                       |
|-----------------------------|------------------------------|
| Class name hota hai         | Koi bhi naam ho sakta hai    |
| No return type              | Return type hota hai         |
| Auto call hota hai          | Call manually karna padta hai |
| Object initialization       | Object ke behavior ko define karta hai |

---

## ðŸ“Œ Practice Idea:

```java
class Car {
    String brand;
    int year;

    // Constructor
    public Car(String brand, int year) {
        this.brand = brand;
        this.year = year;
    }

    public void showDetails() {
        System.out.println("Brand: " + brand + ", Year: " + year);
    }
}
```

```java
Car c1 = new Car("Honda", 2022);
c1.showDetails();
```

